---
import LandingLayout from "../../layouts/LandingLayout.astro";
---

<LandingLayout
	title="Peer"
	description="OpenAPI that stays true to the code — bidirectional scaffold and emit."
	slug="peer"
>
	<main id="main" class="lp-peer">
		<section class="hero" aria-label="Hero">
			<div class="hero-inner">
				<div class="hero-copy">
					<div class="brand-mark">
						<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="" width="40" height="40">
						Routa
						<span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					</div>
					<h1 class="headline">OpenAPI that stays true to the code</h1>
					<p class="lede">
						Edit the Zod contract or the OpenAPI peer. Regenerate the other. Spec and source are
						equals — not a one-way export.
					</p>
					<div class="cta-row">
						<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/">Get started</a>
						<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/Routa-ts/Routa">GitHub</a>
					</div>
					<div class="cli" data-cmd="pnpm create routa-ts@latest">
						<span>$ pnpm create routa-ts@latest</span>
						<button type="button">Copy</button>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="dual">
					<div class="code-panel">
						<div class="code-panel__bar"><span>CreateUserSchema</span><span>zod →</span></div>
						<pre><code><span class="kw">export const</span> CreateUserSchema = z.object({"{"}
  email: z.string().email(),
  name: z.string().min(<span class="str">1</span>),
{"}"});

<span class="cm">// createRoute input.body</span>
<span class="cm">// responses.success → UserSchema</span></code></pre>
					</div>

					<div class="bridge" aria-hidden="true">
						<svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" aria-hidden="true">
							<path d="M8 12 H28 M28 12 L22 8 M28 12 L22 16" />
							<path class="reverse" d="M32 28 H12 M12 28 L18 24 M12 28 L18 32" />
						</svg>
						<span>bidirectional</span>
					</div>

					<div class="code-panel">
						<div class="code-panel__bar"><span>openapi.yaml</span><span>← spec</span></div>
						<pre><code>paths:
  /users:
    post:
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: <span class="str">"#/components/..."</span>
      responses:
        <span class="str">"201"</span>:
          description: success</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="section-inner">
				<p class="section-kicker">Either direction</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">Scaffold or emit — then check</h2>
				<p class="section-lede">
					Start from an OpenAPI file and scaffold routes, or write contracts first and emit the
					spec. <code class="mono">routa check</code> keeps them honest.
				</p>
				<ul class="pillars">
					<li>
						<strong>Scaffold from OpenAPI</strong>
						<p>
							Bootstrap route files and schemas from <code class="mono">.yaml</code> /
							<code class="mono">.json</code>.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Emit from source</strong>
						<p>Contracts project to OpenAPI without a separate hand-maintained doc.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Drift fails</strong>
						<p>CI-friendly check: source and peer must agree.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Filesystem routes</strong>
						<p>The scaffold lands where the URL lives — folders as segments.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Typed middleware</strong>
						<p>Lattice context stays in the graph either way.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Hono + Zod</strong>
						<p>Runtime and schemas you already trust.</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<ul class="built-on" style="margin-top: 2rem">
					<li>Hono</li>
					<li>Zod</li>
					<li>OpenAPI</li>
					<li>TypeScript</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="v0-note">
					<strong>v0</strong>
					— bidirectional is a peer relationship, not a marketing export button.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="close">
			<div class="close-inner">
				<div>
					<h2>OpenAPI workflow</h2>
					<p>Scaffold, emit, and keep the peer in lockstep.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/">Documentation</a>
					<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/landings/">All options</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</LandingLayout>
